-283-million-from-investors-including-everbright-jd-com-and-wanda |publisher=KrAsia |accessdate=13 August 2019 |date=13 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=How Smart Cities and Homes Will Take China Into the Future |url=https://fortune.com/2019/11/07/china-smart-cities/ |publisher=Fortune |accessdate=18 November 2019 |date=18 November 2019}}</ref>. Terminus has its head office in Beijing with research and development offices in Chongqing, Shanghai, Wuhan and Shenzhen<ref name=\"ForbesNina\">{{cite web |last1=Xiang |first1=Nina |title=Chinese Unicorn Terminus Combines AI And IoT To Empower Smarter Cities |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/ninaxiang/2019/03/05/chinese-unicorn-terminus-combines-ai-and-iot-to-empower-smarter-cities/#3e2f4d972bc7 |publisher=Forbes |accessdate=5 March 2019 |date=5 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Chinese AIoT Solution Provider Terminus Closes $283M Series C1 Round |last1=Wang |first1=Eudora |url=https://www.chinamoneynetwork.com/2019/08/12/chinese-aiot-solution-unicorn-terminus-closes-283m-series-c1-round |publisher=China Money Network |accessdate=12 August 2019 |date=12 August 2019}}</ref>.\n\nInvestors in the company include [[IDG Capital]], [[CITIC]], [[JD.com]], and [[iFlytek]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Crunchbase - Terminus Technologies - Investors |url=https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/terminus-technologies-co#section-investors |website=www.crunchbase.com |publisher=Crunchbase}}</ref>.\n\nIts products and services include cloud platforms, edge computing, intelligent hardware, AIoT Solutions, Robotics solutions, smart devices, communication modules, data management platforms and mobile applications<ref name=\"ForbesNina\" /><ref name=\"BeijingPolice\">{{cite web |last1=Fu |first1=Yingwei |title=Beijing Police Deparment Signs Robots Agreement with Terminus |url=https://equalocean.com/iot/20181226-bjpd-signs-robots-agreement-with-terminus |website=www.equalocean.com |publisher=Equal Ocean |accessdate=26 December 2018}}</